};

var DEFAULT_CTX  = 4;   // default context size (story paragraphs) for image prompt architect

var DEFAULT_ARCH = "You are an expert cinematic director translating a narrative scene into a precise image generation prompt for a hybrid text-to-image AI.\n\nAnalyze the provided scene and character data, then output a prompt following this exact structure:\n\n1. CORE TAGS: Start with 10-15 comma-separated Danbooru tags establishing the baseline. Include subject counts (e.g., 1girl, 1boy), rating (e.g., rating: general), camera angles (e.g., dutch angle, from below), lighting (e.g., cinematic lighting, sunbeams), and environment traits.\n2. ACTION & ATMOSPHERE: Follow immediately with 1 to 2 vivid sentences of natural language describing exactly what the characters are doing, their expressions, the mood, and the background details.\n3. CHARACTER INTEGRATION: You MUST seamlessly integrate the specific visual traits of any identified characters into the tags or the prose.\n\nOutput ONLY the final prompt text. Do not include headers, bullet points, introductory text, or commentary.";

var DEFAULT_NOTE = "[System Note: This chat interface supports image attachments. When your character wants to send a selfie, share a picture of their surroundings, or show the user an object, append an image attachment to your message on a new line using this exact format: > [Image: comma-separated visual tags]\nThe tags must be concise visual descriptors (character name, clothing, pose, expression, setting, and lighting). Always include the character's name so their specific appearance is applied.\nExample message:\nI finally made it to the cafe! It's so cute here, wish you were with me.\n[Image: Sarah, smiling, holding a coffee cup, sitting at a cafe table, wearing a cozy oversized sweater, sunlit window background] ]";

